---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { tools } from "../data/tools";
import { CATEGORIES } from "../types";
---

<Layout title="About — Awesome Agent IDEs">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-6">About This Project</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-6 text-text-muted">
      <p class="text-lg">
        The "agent IDE" space exploded in early 2026. There are now {tools.length}+ tools across
        {CATEGORIES.length} distinct categories — orchestrators, terminals, AI-native IDEs, CLI agents,
        VS Code extensions, cloud platforms, and process monitors.
      </p>

      <p>
        The problem: people compare terminals to orchestrators to IDEs, which makes every
        "which should I use?" conversation frustrating. Most comparisons flatten everything
        into one list.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text mt-10 mb-4">The Insight</h2>
      <p>
        <strong class="text-text">The taxonomy IS the product.</strong> The space has at least 4 distinct
        layers, and helping someone understand WHICH LAYER they need is 80% of the value.
        Once you know you need an orchestrator (not a terminal), the comparison within that
        category is straightforward.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text mt-10 mb-4">How It Works</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
        <li>All data is stored as structured TypeScript/JSON in the repository</li>
        <li>Every entry has a <code class="text-accent bg-surface px-1">lastVerified</code> date</li>
        <li>Updates happen via pull requests — anyone can contribute</li>
        <li>The site is statically generated with Astro and deployed on Vercel</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text mt-10 mb-4">Contributing</h2>
      <p>
        Know a tool that's missing? See outdated information? The best way to contribute
        is to open a pull request on GitHub. Each tool is a single entry in
        <code class="text-accent bg-surface px-1">src/data/tools.ts</code>.
      </p>
      <p>Required fields for new entries:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-sm">
        <li><code class="text-accent bg-surface px-1">slug</code> — URL-safe identifier</li>
        <li><code class="text-accent bg-surface px-1">name</code>, <code class="text-accent bg-surface px-1">url</code>, <code class="text-accent bg-surface px-1">description</code></li>
        <li><code class="text-accent bg-surface px-1">primaryCategory</code> — one of: orchestrator, terminal, ide, cli-agent, extension, cloud, monitor</li>
        <li><code class="text-accent bg-surface px-1">platforms</code>, <code class="text-accent bg-surface px-1">license</code>, <code class="text-accent bg-surface px-1">pricing</code>, <code class="text-accent bg-surface px-1">status</code></li>
        <li><code class="text-accent bg-surface px-1">lastVerified</code> — the date you confirmed the data</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text mt-10 mb-4">Roadmap</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
        <li>Side-by-side comparison page (<code class="text-accent bg-surface px-1">/compare?tools=a,b,c</code>)</li>
        <li>Knowledge graph visualization with relationship edges</li>
        <li>Automated GitHub star tracking</li>
        <li>"Build Your Stack" workflow recommender</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="mt-10 pt-6 border-t border-border">
        <p class="text-sm">
          Built by <a href="https://github.com/mulyoved" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover">@mulyoved</a>.
          Inspired by <a href="https://bestofjs.org" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover">Best of JS</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
